        <num>CC 1809</num>
        <heading>1809.  Choice belongs to the obligor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1809.  Choice belongs to the obligor
When an obligation is alternative, the choice of the item of performance belongs to the obligor unless it has been expressly or impliedly granted to the obligee.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109046</p>
